    "text": "SUBSCRIBE\nTHAILAND WORLD BUSINESS OPINION AUTO LIFE LEARNING TRAVEL MORE+\nMOST RECENT\n15:15\nPatong hill road to fully reopen Dec 25\n14:45\nChina announces nationwide loosening of Covid restrictions\n14:27\nEconomy firmly on recovery path, Arkhom tells Bangkok Post forum\n13:52\nInflation slowing as supply increases\n13:40\nVietnamese EV maker VinFast files for US IPO\n13:20\nPrime time or Netflix? Streaming wars come to Thailand\n10:51\nMore ganja seized on Mekong river bank\n10:36\nTimber trader fatally shot, pickup burned\nTOP STORIES\nBUSINESS\nBrakes on inflation\nImproved food supply and price controls help rein in the soaring cost of living, with inflation slowing for the third consecutive month.\n13:52\nTHAILAND\nMore flights, please\nPrime Minister Prayut Chan-o-cha ordered the Transport Ministry to directly contact international airlines to increase flights into the country following a surge in demand.\n04:21 26\nTHAILAND\nPheu Thai's promise to hike wages under fire\nThe Pheu Thai Party kicked off its election campaign with promises of lifting the daily minimum wage to 600 baht and the minimum monthly salary for those with a bachelor's degree to 25,000 baht.\n05:00 44\nTHAILAND\nMingkwan tipped to be PPRP's prime minister pick\nMingkwan Sangsuwan, former leader of the New Economics Party (NEP), who officially joined the ruling Palang Pracharath Party (PPRP) on Tuesday, is expected to be named one of its prime ministerial candidates.\n04:00 2\nTHAILAND\nPolicy-level corruption rife, anti-graft body says\nPolicy-level corruption remains rife in Thailand despite progress being made to address the issue, according to the Anti-Corruption Organisation of Thailand (ACT).\n06:00 12\nBUSINESS\nTravel agents urge region to reopen\nOngoing travel restrictions and entry requirements in some countries are the most critical obstacles to expanding the tourism sector.\n04:39 2\nTHAILAND\n'2 more years'\nGen Prayut Chan-o-cha says he wants to stay prime m